The fluid flow velocities and shear rates corresponding to each positioner and heater voltage settings were simulated following procedures described in refs. 37,38 and in the “Methods” section. One example of the fluid flow velocities and shear rates, as shown in Supplementary Fig. 2, evolves with decreasing temperatures and shows a distribution; it is largest along the surface of the sample in a direction about \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
